      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TURBO TORQUE (6) has had a few chances but has remarkably hit the top-five in 14 of his past 15 starts and is usually thereabouts. Has placed two of three over this track and trip and gets in well at the weights with the 2kg claim. Gets his chance to break through here. Former Gollan galloper NAVY KISS (5) just found one better here when having his first run for the new stable and will have come on with that effort now under the belt. Again gets the services of Wiggins in the irons and can play a major role in the outcome. JETHRO (8) has gotten better with each run and looks to be improving with racing. In the mix. CHECK ONE TWO (7) has placed in her past three outings and this is not an overly strong affair. One for the exotics players. SAILING SOLO (9) is next in line in a race with only a handful of hopes.",
